exercise.name: Recover
exercise.description: Use this time to catch your breath. It will help you get more out of what's next

exercise.name: Dumbbell Incline Row
exercise.description: Adjust the incline bench up one notch.. Lie facedown with your sternum at the edge of the bench.. Lift your chest slightly,, and squeeze your elbows back to bring the dumbbells up.. Pause at the top,, and lower under control..

exercise.name: Bicep Curls

exercise.name: Hanging Leg Extensions
exercise.description: Grab onto a bar with your palms facing forward. Make sure your feet are off the ground. Then slowly lift both your legs straight-out until your feet reach hip height. Then slowly lower them back down.

exercise.name: Tricep Dips
exercise.description: Start with your arms extended and hands on the edge of the bench. You feet should be resting on your heels. Lower down until your upper arms are parallel with the floor, push back up by straightening your arms. To increase the difficulty, put your feet up on a second bench.
